name: Atul Deshpande
aboutUs: Although I have had "Public Selection Commission Job Offer as Class -1 office,r I selected teaching as my career primarily because of passion for this noble profession. Now, I have been teaching for more than 25 years and that has been at varied levels starting from 12th to post-graduate and M.Phil along with Ph. D. Classes. In teaching the most fascinating thing is "changing and most heterogeneous students' population which compels you to preferably succumb to a differentiated teaching-learning practices. As methodology I have used and been using a wide -spectrum of pedagogical devices such as "class-room", "case-studies", "role-play", "simulation games(if required)", "peer-sharing", "presentations", One-to-One interaction", "class-room interactive sessions etc. In this process I emphasize simplicity, conceptual understanding, problem-solving techniques, real-world examples, writing skills development, analytical- skills development etc. Since my basic expertise lies in economics, finance and international business development along with statistics as a tool to understand and analyze problem, any topics originating from these areas attract me and I love to deal with them. I have stated earlier that I have practically taught students' age groups ranging from 18 to 40-45 who are essentially pursuing their Ph.D programmes. Till this date, many of my students are abroad doing their MS programme at reputed universities. I have been awarded with the "best teacher prize" by the Pune Municipal Corporation and many of my research papers are showered with "best research paper awards". I  strongly believe that teaching-learning process is truly dynamic and challenging because of the changing content and the use of technology.

name: Vikas Kumar Jha
aboutUs: Sound mathematical approach and command on branches of physics which require significant mathematical skills. I have been teaching Maths & Physics to 11th & 12th grade students aspiring to get through IIT-JEE for past 6 years at various private coaching academies in differently designed Engineering entrance courses and even on one to one basis to a few of them with fair amount of success. Mathematics and numerical Physics requires fundamental building & scientific aptitude to be developed at a young age or else students struggle to cope up with them for ever. There is no point mugging up with problem solving techniques over & over again if the fundamentals are not cleared thoroughly. Solving too many problems without understanding the concepts properly won't give desired results. So I rather focus to work on fundamental building & conceptual clarity ,which gradually help students develop mathematical & scientific aptitude over a period of time (a must for any serious IIT-JEE candidate). In spite of being an Engineer & Mba,my inclination towards teaching mathematics that I developed early in my Engineering days brought me back to it. Being from Mechanical engineering background,I have also been teaching Engineering Mathematics-1,2 & 3 ,Engineering Mechanics,Thermodynamics & Strength of materials to first & second year degree students of B.Tech courses of various engineering colleges for last 6 years. For those willing to push the extra yard,I am always ready to put in extra !!
